# Rule: ROADMAP.md

`ROADMAP.md` is the **phase plan**. Each phase row has these
columns:

| Column | Source |
|---|---|
| Phase | `Phase N — <name>`. |
| ADR(s) | `docs/adr/NNNN-<slug>.md` ids that ship in this phase. |
| Component(s) | `SPEC.md` rows that this phase activates (i.e. the row's package becomes non‑empty). |
| Status | `shipped` / `in progress` / `planned`. The row that ships the bootstrap (Phase 0) starts as `shipped`. |

The doc must:

- list phases in order, no gaps;
- never describe a phase without citing at least one ADR or
  marking it `planned` and saying which ADR will justify it;
- stay under ~100 lines.

A new phase row is added by the PR that introduces the first ADR
for the phase; a phase is marked `shipped` in the same PR that
closes the phase (the PR's last commit).

## Template

```markdown
# ROADMAP.md — phases

> Read AGENTS.md §3 before extending this document. Each phase row
> is justified by at least one ADR in `docs/adr/`.

| Phase | ADR(s) | Component(s) | Status |
|-------|--------|--------------|--------|
| Phase 0 — Bootstrap | (none — tooling) | (none — no components yet) | shipped |
| Phase 1 — Supervisor | ADR NNNN | Supervisor | in progress / planned |
| … | … | … | … |
```